<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Oxyria</i> <i>digyna</i> is characteristically present in the herbaceous layer with <i>Cystopteris</i> <i>fragilis</i>, <i>Draba</i> <i>lemmonii</i>, <i>Saxifraga</i> <i>tolmiei</i> and <i>Senecio</i> <i>fremontii</i>. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 20 cm; cover is open. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> North-facing aspects, headwalls in rock cervices and unstable, wet snow beds, moving talus where snow remains on the ground until late July or early August. The USFWS Wetland Inventory (1996 national list) recognizes <i>Oxyria digyna</i> as a FACW plant. </div>
</div>

		
